divs: Sighting DetailsSighting Report: Thursday, June 16, I was out in a field behind my house. There were only a few clouds in the sky and alot of "stars" to be seen. After about five minutes of sky watching, I realized that there were too many stars that appeared to be moving. I thought that it was only generalized to a few "stars", but after looking further, I realized what appeared to be @30 some stars that were moving. I thought they could be planes as I am on the flight pattern of Toledo airport, but there were also lights that definitely were planes. As I watched the star lights, they would stop, reverse and speed forward. I more I looked back across the sky, the more moving "stars" I saw. I was very freaky. I went inside. I am going back tonight if there are no clouds.
